{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:49:51.173318", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: EBGP-based Clos fabric with super-spine (AS 65000), spines, and leaves. Each leaf connects to a single host and advertises a /24 (10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24).\\n- Scope: Hosts pc_0_0 and pc_0_1; routers leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0.\\n\\nSummary Assessment\\n- Fabric control plane is healthy: All EBGP sessions between leaves, spines, and super-spine are established, and routes are consistently present in all routers.\\n- Data plane appears healthy across the fabric for active hosts: pc_0_1 has end-to-end reachability to remote subnets with low latency and no loss.\\n- Anomaly: pc_0_0 is not reachable and has no network configuration (no NIC IP, no routes). The corresponding leaf access port shows no traffic. This is isolated to the endpoint/link segment for 10.0.0.0/24 and does not indicate a fabric-wide issue.\\n\\nDetailed Findings\\n\\n1) Reachability\\n- pc_0_1 can reach remote pod hosts (e.g., 10.1.2.2, 10.1.3.2) with 0% loss; RTT ~1–5 ms.\\n- pc_0_0 cannot initiate ping (error: “Network is unreachable”), and is not reachable from pc_0_1.\\n\\n2) Host States\\n- pc_0_1\\n  - IP: 10.0.1.2/24 on eth0; default route via 10.0.1.1.\\n  - Interface state: eth0 UP; routing present.\\n- pc_0_0\\n  - Only loopback is present; no eth0 listed, no IP address configured, no routes.\\n  - Any attempt to ping fails locally with “Network is unreachable”.\\n\\n3) Leaf Routers (Host-Facing)\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (serves 10.0.1.0/24):\\n  - Interface 10.0.1.1/24 on eth4; has RX/TX counters consistent with host traffic.\\n  - IP route table includes all 10.0.x and 10.1.x learned via EBGP; BGP peers up with spines.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (serves 10.0.0.0/24):\\n  - Interface 10.0.0.1/24 on eth4; RX/TX counters show 0 packets (no host traffic seen).\\n  - IP route table includes all 10.0.x and 10.1.x learned via EBGP; BGP peers up with spines.\\n\\n4) Spine and Super-Spine Routers\\n- spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1:\\n  - EBGP neighbors up to super-spine and leaves.\\n  - Routes for 10.0.0.0/24, 10.0.1.0/24, and multiple remote 10.1.x/24s installed with ECMP where expected.\\n- super_spine_router_0:\\n  - EBGP neighbors up to spines; routing tables show all leaf subnets present and consistent.\\n\\n5) Topology vs Interface Numbering (Observation)\\n- Provided topology states host links on leaf eth2. In the running configs, host subnets are bound to eth4 on both leaves. pc_0_1 is operational via leaf_router_0_1:eth4; leaf_router_0_0:eth4 shows no traffic. This suggests the effective host-facing interface is eth4, not eth2, for both leaves.\\n\\nAnomaly Detection\\n- pc_0_0 is not participating in the network:\\n  - No L3 configuration on the host (no IP, no default route, interface not present/UP).\\n  - The corresponding leaf host-facing port (leaf_router_0_0 eth4 with 10.0.0.1/24) shows no traffic.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- The fault domain is localized to the access edge for 10.0.0.0/24:\\n  - Endpoint pc_0_0 and/or its directly connected link to leaf_router_0_0.\\n  - The routed fabric (leaves, spines, super-spine) is functioning normally.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Endpoint misconfiguration/unprovisioned state on pc_0_0:\\n  - Missing/Down host interface and absent IP configuration (no eth0 present in system inventory, only loopback).\\n  - Consequently, no ARP/L2/L3 traffic reaches leaf_router_0_0 eth4, and pc_0_0 cannot route (hence “Network is unreachable”).\\n- This is not a BGP or fabric routing issue.\\n\\nEvidence (key excerpts)\\n- pc_0_0: ip addr shows only lo; ip route empty; ping errors “Network is unreachable.”\\n- pc_0_1: eth0 UP, 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1; successful ping to remote subnets.\\n- leaf_router_0_0: eth4 10.0.0.1/24; RX/TX = 0; BGP summary shows all peers up and prefixes received.\\n- leaf_router_0_1: eth4 10.0.1.1/24; RX/TX > 0; BGP peers up and prefixes received.\\n- Spines/super-spine: EBGP sessions established; consistent routes installed.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The data center fabric is healthy and correctly exchanging routes.\\n- The only identified abnormal behavior is isolated to pc_0_0, which lacks a configured/active network interface and IP, resulting in complete loss of connectivity for 10.0.0.0/24’s host., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='db05f184-1630-45bc-b405-2e55dd826464'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
